# ============================================================================
# DE10-Nano Kernel Configuration
# ============================================================================
# This is a reference configuration file
# The actual kernel config will be generated from the kernel source
# using: make ARCH=arm socfpga_defconfig
# ============================================================================
#
# Key configuration options needed:
# - FPGA Manager support
# - UIO support (for advanced FPGA access)
# - Network support (Ethernet) - STMMAC driver for HPS GMAC
# - SSH/network tools support
# - Calculator driver (if using kernel module)
#
# Ethernet Configuration (HPS GMAC):
# The DE10-Nano uses HPS Ethernet (GMAC), not FPGA Ethernet.
# Required kernel options (should be in default socfpga_defconfig):
#   CONFIG_STMMAC_ETH=y          # STMMAC Ethernet driver
#   CONFIG_DWMAC_GENERIC=y       # Generic DWMAC support
#   CONFIG_DWMAC_SOCFPGA=y       # SoCFPGA-specific support
#
# To customize kernel configuration:
#   cd linux-socfpga
#   make ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabihf- menuconfig
#
# This file serves as documentation of required options.
# The actual .config will be generated from kernel source defaults.
#
# Note: The default socfpga_defconfig from the kernel source should already
# include Ethernet driver support. If Ethernet doesn't work, verify these
# options are enabled in the generated .config file.
